<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I tried the quest tonight as well.  I noted the repaired faction with Roror who now cons as Indifferent, but when I handed over my writhing hay to Shakey he gave me faction and experience but NO ITEM.  For all the many hours I have spent talking to GMs about this quest over the past few months, you would think that they would just send in a GM to hand over the belts and harvesters.  But Oh No... we simply cannot have people completing quests and getting items they have earned...that would be too easy.  I think I get it now.  The quest for the Belt or Harvester revolves around GMs.  The most difficult and time consuming part of the quest (Verant is more clever and sneaky than I would ever have guessed) is getting a GM to talk to you, agree with you, then finally patch the problem, only to insert another bug to extend the quest and therefore extend the fun of attempting to complete such a quest =)  Thank you Verant for turning a simple Quest into an EVERQuest!<BR>
<BR>
Vitharr Crepuscule<BR>
